# Leacme.AllCoiner

**Leacme AllCoiner** is a cross-platform desktop application able to run on Windows, MacOS, and Linux. It is build using [Microsoft .NET](https://github.com/dotnet/core) platform and [Avalonia UI](https://github.com/AvaloniaUI/Avalonia) framework.

This application features the ability to monitor the current activity of various Cryptocoins and get their market rate in the currency of your choice.

![index](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6654513/71701526-256da900-2d87-11ea-9455-57514e21ae78.png)
![][image_screenshot]

## Application Compiling

The desktop application can be compiled into an executable with [.NET 3.1](https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download/dotnet-core/3.1) by navigating to `Leacme.App.AllCoiner` folder and running:
```
dotnet publish --configuration Release -p:CopyOutputSymbolsToPublishDirectory=false -p:PublishSingleFile=true -p:LeacmeOutputType=winexe --runtime win-x64
```
Note: `win-x64` can be replaced with other runtimes such as `linux-x64`, or `osx-x64`, for more runtimes see [RID Catalog](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/rid-catalog)

## Application Usage

Choose which Cryptocoin you want to get the rate for by beginning to type in the Cryptocoin box and select the matching coin. Select the currency to which you want to convert on the right and click Convert. The bottom panel provides information for the Top 20 Cryptocoins.

## Library Usage

The applicatin library can also be build and used separately by navigating to `Leacme.Lib.AllCoiner` folder and running `dotnet build`. This will create a .dll library that can be copied into the directory where your .csproj is located. Be sure as well to add the following line to your .csproj file to point to the location of the library:
```
<ItemGroup><Reference Include="Leacme.Lib.AllCoiner.dll"><HintPath>Leacme.Lib.AllCoiner.dll</HintPath></Reference></ItemGroup>
```
It can then be added and used within your project with `var library = new Leacme.Lib.AllCoiner.Library();`
